CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1781075106
OL,3,CKemi Badenoch pledges to scrap public
OL,4,Csector equalities law
OL,6,FSpeaking at the Institute for
OL,7,FGovernment, Badenoch claimed that the
OL,8,FNottingham stabbings, the Southport
OL,9,Fattack, and the Manchester Arena
OL,10,Fbombing could have been stopped if
OL,11,Fpublic authorities did not fear being
OL,12,Fcalled racist.
OL,14,FBadenoch said: "All these crimes could
OL,15,Fhave been stopped if people had
OL,16,Fintervened instead of having a fear of
OL,17,Fbeing called racist.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1781075106
OL,3,CKemi Badenoch pledges to scrap public
OL,4,Csector equalities law
OL,6,F"We would not have had so many girls
OL,7,Fabused by rape gangs if local
OL,8,Fauthorities had not looked away
OL,9,Fbecause they were too scared to point
OL,10,Fout the obvious."
OL,12,FShe added: "If the security guards at
OL,13,Fthe Manchester Arena weren't afraid of
OL,14,Fbeing accused of racial profiling, we
OL,15,Fwouldn't have seen a bomber walk into
OL,16,Fthe venue unchecked.
OL,26,@rD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
